1
00:00:14,541 --> 00:00:16,500
[sighs]

2
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:19,125
It's too bad the others
didn't want to join me.

3
00:00:20,083 --> 00:00:23,291
No, I'm gonna pass.
I don't like the baths.

4
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:25,500
It's like the spirits
of air, fire, and water

5
00:00:25,583 --> 00:00:27,083
are all mixed up together,

6
00:00:27,166 --> 00:00:29,083
which always feels
a little off-putting.

7
00:00:29,166 --> 00:00:32,041
Personally, I'd rather unwind
with a little food and drink.

8
00:00:32,125 --> 00:00:34,500
There's nothing better
for a fatigued soul

9
00:00:34,583 --> 00:00:36,416
than a delectable
wheel of cheese.

10
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:38,625
And what about you,
Goblin Slayer?

11
00:00:38,708 --> 00:00:40,458
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I have to mail something.

12
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,708
Like a letter?
Really?

13
00:00:42,791 --> 00:00:44,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes.

14
00:00:45,916 --> 00:00:47,708
He's so private.

15
00:00:47,791 --> 00:00:50,791
I never have any idea
what's going on inside his head,

16
00:00:50,875 --> 00:00:52,375
which makes sense, I guess.

17
00:00:52,458 --> 00:00:56,250
It's only been a few months
since we met in that cave.

18
00:00:56,333 --> 00:00:59,000
♪

19
00:00:59,083 --> 00:01:01,041
Huh.

20
00:01:01,125 --> 00:01:02,458
[gasps]

21
00:01:02,541 --> 00:01:06,916
If he hadn't shown up,
then I would have...

22
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:09,041
He saved my life.

23
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:11,833
-[WOMAN] Hello?
-[gasps]

24
00:01:17,291 --> 00:01:20,000
I hope you don't mind
if I join you for a quick soak.

25
00:02:52,291 --> 00:02:55,708
I apologize if I startled
you just now.

26
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:58,750
I'm afraid my duties
kept me working late.

27
00:02:58,833 --> 00:03:00,166
[gasps]

28
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,041
-Uh...
-Huh?

29
00:03:06,125 --> 00:03:08,291
It's fine.

30
00:03:08,375 --> 00:03:11,125
Your scars...
Are you okay?

31
00:03:11,208 --> 00:03:12,875
Oh, these old things?

32
00:03:12,958 --> 00:03:15,625
They're the results of
a foolish mistake on my part.

33
00:03:15,708 --> 00:03:18,458
My foes snuck up behind me
and hit me in the head.

34
00:03:18,541 --> 00:03:20,875
I can't believe that was
more than ten years ago now.

35
00:03:20,958 --> 00:03:23,625
Still, even if it was
a while ago...

36
00:03:24,583 --> 00:03:27,000
you probably find yourself
thinking about it.

37
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:30,541
[SWORD MAIDEN] I could tell
that you're a kind person.

38
00:03:30,625 --> 00:03:32,500
When I tell
most people my story,

39
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:34,791
they usually end up
apologizing for asking.

40
00:03:34,875 --> 00:03:36,916
It wasn't my place
to bring up.

41
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,833
-[SWORD MAIDEN laughs]
-Huh?

42
00:03:38,916 --> 00:03:41,416
Please don't worry,
I actually find it refreshing.

43
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,000
[PRIESTESS sighs]

44
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:45,708
These eyes have seen
many things.

45
00:03:45,791 --> 00:03:48,250
More than you could
possibly imagine, I'd wager.

46
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:52,291
-Both beauty and horrors.
-[gasps]

47
00:03:54,916 --> 00:03:56,500
[SWORD MAIDEN]
That man with you?

48
00:03:56,583 --> 00:03:57,541
[PRIESTESS]
Huh?

49
00:03:58,875 --> 00:04:01,833
The one who refers to himself
as Goblin Slayer.

50
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:04,291
He appears to be
a dependable fellow.

51
00:04:04,375 --> 00:04:06,375
That's very true.

52
00:04:06,458 --> 00:04:09,041
He's also so brave, too.

53
00:04:09,125 --> 00:04:10,916
It seems your search
is going well.

54
00:04:13,208 --> 00:04:16,500
But... you should prepare
yourself.

55
00:04:16,583 --> 00:04:19,083
Someday I'm sure
he'll disappear.

56
00:04:19,166 --> 00:04:20,916
-Trust me.
[PRIESTESS gasps]

57
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:28,375
What do you mean?
Have you...?

58
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:31,541
[SWORD MAIDEN] Don't stay in
too long, or you'll grow faint.

59
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:37,916
[PRIESTESS] Her scars.
She knows. I can tell.

60
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,333
She knows what
the goblins are like.

61
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:44,333
[voices chattering]

62
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:52,375
Will you look at her.
That there's a high elf.

63
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:55,291
You don't say? I've never
laid eyes on one of them before.

64
00:04:55,375 --> 00:04:58,708
That body. I wouldn't mind
adventuring with her, you know?

65
00:04:58,791 --> 00:05:01,416
[ARCHER scoffs]
Men are disgusting.

66
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:02,958
Oh, there you are.

67
00:05:03,041 --> 00:05:05,666
Sorry to make you wait.
Did you send your letter?

68
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yeah. I formally requested

69
00:05:07,666 --> 00:05:09,958
that a fellow adventurer
take it to town.

70
00:05:10,041 --> 00:05:12,000
Now that I think about it,

71
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:15,333
I don't know that I've written
a letter to someone before ever.

72
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:18,083
What do you say in one?
Just tell people you're alive?

73
00:05:18,166 --> 00:05:19,958
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
That's basically the point,

74
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:21,166
like a report.

75
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:22,875
[ARCHER]
Which means I bet he's sending

76
00:05:22,958 --> 00:05:24,833
updates to that farm girl.

77
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:26,958
[ARCHER]
Well, well, Orcbolg.

78
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:29,125
Sounds like you care
about people after all.

79
00:05:29,208 --> 00:05:30,541
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Something's wrong.

80
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,041
[ARCHER]
Yeah? What's that?

81
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:34,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER] This town has
a vast sewer system,

82
00:05:34,833 --> 00:05:37,208
but there are no quests
to kill giant rats.

83
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:39,666
Huh. Figured he wasn't
from the city.

84
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:42,458
Only vermin that's infesting
this town is right here.

85
00:05:42,541 --> 00:05:44,375
I guess that is kind of strange.

86
00:05:44,458 --> 00:05:46,208
Or there was
a big hunt recently.

87
00:05:46,291 --> 00:05:48,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Hmm.

88
00:05:48,791 --> 00:05:52,083
[ARCHER] Hey, wait.
Where are you off to now?

89
00:05:52,166 --> 00:05:54,083
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
There's something I need to buy.

90
00:05:54,166 --> 00:05:56,291
All right.
Never too late to shop.

91
00:05:56,375 --> 00:05:58,416
[canary singing]

92
00:06:02,333 --> 00:06:04,000
[singing]

93
00:06:04,083 --> 00:06:05,541
What is this thing?

94
00:06:05,625 --> 00:06:07,291
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
You don't know what a bird is?

95
00:06:07,375 --> 00:06:10,000
-I mean, why'd you buy a pet?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] It's a canary.

96
00:06:10,083 --> 00:06:12,166
That's what you had
to go shopping for?

97
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,375
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yes.

98
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:16,875
[ARCHER]
Wait. Is this like that scroll?

99
00:06:16,958 --> 00:06:20,291
If I touch the bird, will it
blow up or put a curse on me?

100
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:21,916
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Do you really think a canary

101
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:23,541
would be able to kill
someone like you?

102
00:06:23,625 --> 00:06:26,250
[PRIESTESS] I think there's
a communication issue here.

103
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:28,625
She's wondering why you brought
the canary underground

104
00:06:28,708 --> 00:06:30,166
with us to begin with.

105
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:32,250
[GOBLIN SLAYER sighs]
Canaries panic when they smell

106
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:34,083
even the slightest hint
of poison gas.

107
00:06:34,166 --> 00:06:37,250
-Poison? Way down here?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yeah.

108
00:06:37,333 --> 00:06:40,666
The goblins in this nest appear
to have been educated.

109
00:06:40,750 --> 00:06:42,458
It wouldn't surprise me
if they could use

110
00:06:42,541 --> 00:06:44,916
the defense systems
in these ruins.

111
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,583
[PRIEST]
Sir Goblin Slayer,

112
00:06:46,666 --> 00:06:48,791
where did you acquire
such knowledge?

113
00:06:48,875 --> 00:06:50,416
[GOBLIN SLAYERS]
From miners.

114
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,833
Most people in this world
are more intelligent than I am,

115
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:54,875
unless it's about
slaying goblins.

116
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:58,125
So, Beard-cutter, where are
we headed this morning?

117
00:06:58,208 --> 00:07:00,291
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
We're traveling upstream.

118
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:03,000
That's the direction
their boat came from last time.

119
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,041
[SHAMAN] I see.
That makes sense.

120
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER] We'll do
everything we can

121
00:07:07,750 --> 00:07:09,333
to avoid running into goblins.

122
00:07:09,416 --> 00:07:11,166
That's odd coming from you.

123
00:07:11,250 --> 00:07:14,166
I'm honestly surprised you'd let
any of the goblins pass by.

124
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:15,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I don't plan to.

125
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:18,875
I'm going to take down
their leader, crush their nest,

126
00:07:18,958 --> 00:07:22,333
and slaughter every stray goblin
who escapes into these tunnels.

127
00:07:22,416 --> 00:07:24,083
Do you think
there could be another ogre

128
00:07:24,166 --> 00:07:25,458
or shaman down here?

129
00:07:25,541 --> 00:07:27,791
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I don't know.

130
00:07:30,166 --> 00:07:31,625
[sighs]

131
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:36,041
Although, someday I'm sure
he'll disappear. Trust me.

132
00:07:36,125 --> 00:07:38,041
[sighs]

133
00:07:43,916 --> 00:07:45,458
[PRIEST]
This is where the map ends.

134
00:07:45,541 --> 00:07:47,500
We must forge our own path now.

135
00:07:47,583 --> 00:07:49,625
[doors creaking]

136
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,375
[PRIESTESS]
This place is gigantic.

137
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:57,166
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Traces of soot.

138
00:07:57,250 --> 00:08:01,083
That could possibly mean other
people were down here, recently.

139
00:08:01,166 --> 00:08:03,333
[GOBLIN SLAYER] It hasn't
been used in a long time.

140
00:08:03,416 --> 00:08:05,375
Goblins have excellent
night vision.

141
00:08:05,458 --> 00:08:06,791
They don't need lights.

142
00:08:07,833 --> 00:08:10,000
[PRIEST] They must be
warriors or guards.

143
00:08:10,083 --> 00:08:13,041
No, wait, I believe
these figures to be adventurers.

144
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:16,041
I've heard tales
of the many fearsome battles

145
00:08:16,125 --> 00:08:18,125
that took place
in this area in the past.

146
00:08:18,208 --> 00:08:23,083
This painting is probably four
or 500 years old, at least.

147
00:08:23,166 --> 00:08:26,208
Then, could this actually
be a mass grave?

148
00:08:26,291 --> 00:08:28,791
For the valiant who fought
on the side of order,

149
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:31,291
a final resting place
for heroes,

150
00:08:31,375 --> 00:08:34,458
still standing from
the Age of the Gods.

151
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:35,958
A monument to champions

152
00:08:36,041 --> 00:08:39,166
that's now home
to scores of filthy goblins.

153
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:40,416
I suppose this is
what happens

154
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,625
when everyone forgets
you existed.

155
00:08:42,708 --> 00:08:44,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
None of that matters right now.

156
00:08:44,791 --> 00:08:47,166
There's no need to be
impatient, Beard-cutter.

157
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,500
The goblins will go running
when they see you,

158
00:08:49,583 --> 00:08:52,041
even if they have
to wait a bit longer.

159
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:53,708
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
That would be a problem.

160
00:08:53,791 --> 00:08:56,458
I'd prefer them not to split up.

161
00:08:56,541 --> 00:08:58,916
These hallways are like
some kind of labyrinth.

162
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,875
The builders must've
designed it this way,

163
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:03,375
so that any monsters
who wandered in would get lost,

164
00:09:03,458 --> 00:09:05,333
in the hopes that
the dead warriors buried here

165
00:09:05,416 --> 00:09:06,875
would not be disturbed.

166
00:09:06,958 --> 00:09:09,291
Having to wander around
this place as a lost spirit

167
00:09:09,375 --> 00:09:11,666
would be a cruel fate indeed.

168
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,875
[PRIEST]
Yes, and it would also remove

169
00:09:13,958 --> 00:09:16,500
one from the cycle
of death and rebirth.

170
00:09:16,583 --> 00:09:19,458
We cannot allow the goblins
to confuse our path.

171
00:09:19,541 --> 00:09:22,333
Those dastardly creatures
could attack at any moment.

172
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:24,166
We must remain vigilant.

173
00:09:25,541 --> 00:09:28,291
[PRIESTESS] Might as well start
with this room, I guess.

174
00:09:28,375 --> 00:09:29,708
[ARCHER]
It isn't locked,

175
00:09:29,791 --> 00:09:31,916
and there don't appear
to be any traps,

176
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,708
not on the door at least.

177
00:09:33,791 --> 00:09:35,583
But I'm no expert
on ancient ruins,

178
00:09:35,666 --> 00:09:36,791
so don't get mad at me

179
00:09:36,875 --> 00:09:38,625
if something goes
terribly wrong here.

180
00:09:38,708 --> 00:09:40,625
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Let's go!
-[ARCHER gasps]

181
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:42,541
[doors clatter]

182
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:46,041
[bow string creaking]

183
00:09:46,125 --> 00:09:48,125
-Oh, no, a prisoner!
-[gasps]

184
00:09:48,208 --> 00:09:50,750
[PRIESTESS]
How awful!

185
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:53,875
Huh?

186
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:55,875
-But what's the matter?
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Look.

187
00:09:55,958 --> 00:09:57,125
Huh?

188
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:01,750
[shrieks]

189
00:10:01,833 --> 00:10:03,541
[PRIESTESS whimpers]

190
00:10:03,625 --> 00:10:05,333
[doors creaking]

191
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:07,291
-Huh?
-[doors thud shut]

192
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:08,625
[grunts]

193
00:10:10,166 --> 00:10:11,416
This is not good at all.

194
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,208
They've barred the door
from the outside.

195
00:10:13,291 --> 00:10:15,166
♪

196
00:10:19,333 --> 00:10:20,833
[growls]
They're on us.

197
00:10:20,916 --> 00:10:23,250
[SHAMAN] Looks like
we fell into their hands.

198
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:24,958
No. What do we do?

199
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,750
Goblin Slayer, they have us
completely trapped.

200
00:10:27,833 --> 00:10:30,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Calm down.
We're still alive.

201
00:10:30,208 --> 00:10:31,375
[GOBLINS growl]

202
00:10:31,458 --> 00:10:33,125
-[SHAMAN groans]
-[canary chirping wildly]

203
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:34,125
[ARCHER]
Poison gas!

204
00:10:36,083 --> 00:10:37,375
Oh no!

205
00:10:37,458 --> 00:10:39,291
[PRIEST groans]

206
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:40,916
[canary chirping]

207
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,708
♪

208
00:10:49,708 --> 00:10:51,041
[PRIEST]
Dreadful.

209
00:10:51,125 --> 00:10:54,166
They have us cornered
as though we were rats.

210
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:57,083
In the best-case scenario,
the gas isn't deadly to us,

211
00:10:57,166 --> 00:10:59,416
but it will definitely
slow us down.

212
00:10:59,500 --> 00:11:00,750
There's no way out,

213
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,916
and the gas will fill
the whole room soon!

214
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,916
So. What do we do now?
I can't help us.

215
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,833
I haven't been granted
the miracle to remove poison.

216
00:11:09,916 --> 00:11:11,041
Huh?

217
00:11:11,125 --> 00:11:12,500
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Wrap this in cloth.

218
00:11:12,583 --> 00:11:14,500
Then tie it around your face.

219
00:11:14,583 --> 00:11:16,708
How is a piece of charcoal
going to help?

220
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,500
[GOBLIN SLAYER] It'll protect
you from the poison.

221
00:11:18,583 --> 00:11:20,708
If you have any herbs,
wrap them up with it.

222
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:22,583
Be quick,
or you're dead.

223
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:28,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Quicklime and volcanic earth--

224
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:30,500
mix them together
and block the holes.

225
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:33,416
[SHAMAN] Huh?
This will form concrete!

226
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
It'll be slow to dry.

227
00:11:35,708 --> 00:11:39,125
[SHAMAN] Don't worry.
I know a good weathering spell.

228
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,708
[ARCHER grunts]

229
00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:43,166
[ARCHER] I'm faster. I'll go
around and start plugging.

230
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:45,500
You follow me
with the spell, Dwarf.

231
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:47,041
[SHAMAN]
Understood.

232
00:11:47,125 --> 00:11:50,875
Tick-tock says the clock,
its hands never stop.

233
00:11:50,958 --> 00:11:53,958
Pendulum swing,
time's the thing!

234
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,833
Weathering!

235
00:11:58,166 --> 00:11:59,416
[PRIEST]
Very impressive.

236
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:01,166
It seems you have
a great multitude of wiles

237
00:12:01,250 --> 00:12:02,958
hidden up your sleeve, Sir Mage.

238
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:04,416
We can stop the gas,

239
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,416
but what is it that you intend
for us to do next,

240
00:12:06,500 --> 00:12:07,791
Sir Goblin Slayer?

241
00:12:09,916 --> 00:12:11,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER] We'll push one
of these stone coffins

242
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:13,333
in front of the door
to block it.

243
00:12:13,416 --> 00:12:15,000
Once the poison dissipates,

244
00:12:15,083 --> 00:12:16,958
they're going to come
crashing through.

245
00:12:17,041 --> 00:12:18,291
I'll need help.

246
00:12:18,375 --> 00:12:20,416
[ALL grunting]

247
00:12:23,958 --> 00:12:25,958
[PRIESTESS panting]

248
00:12:27,041 --> 00:12:29,625
[PRIEST] This precaution should
slow them down at least.

249
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:32,458
We've finished blocking up all
the holes so they can't gas us.

250
00:12:32,541 --> 00:12:35,791
That being said, I'm out
of spells for the time being.

251
00:12:35,875 --> 00:12:37,333
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Then take up a weapon.

252
00:12:37,416 --> 00:12:40,083
-[doors rattling]
-[GOBLINS growling]

253
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:46,916
Shall I summon a dragontooth
warrior to aid us in our plight?

254
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,666
-Yes, and I can cast Protection.
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Do it.

255
00:12:52,125 --> 00:12:55,375
[PRIEST] O horns and claws
of our father Iguanodon...

256
00:12:55,458 --> 00:12:58,166
[PRIESTESS] Hear me,
O merciful Earth Mother.

257
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:01,458
Please protect us, the weak,
with your divine light

258
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:02,833
and the sacred power of nature!

259
00:13:02,916 --> 00:13:04,083
[PRIEST]
Come, dragontooth warrior!

260
00:13:04,166 --> 00:13:05,791
Protection!

261
00:13:11,041 --> 00:13:12,291
What happened?

262
00:13:12,375 --> 00:13:14,166
I don't like how quiet
it is out there.

263
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:16,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Since we stopped the holes,

264
00:13:16,208 --> 00:13:18,291
the poison gas
reversed its flow.

265
00:13:18,375 --> 00:13:20,791
I'm sure at least
a few of the goblins died.

266
00:13:20,875 --> 00:13:23,000
-[pounding]
-Huh?

267
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:25,125
-[GOBLINS growling]
-[pounding]

268
00:13:28,083 --> 00:13:29,500
[gasps]

269
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:32,000
[roaring]

270
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,583
[GOBLIN shrieks]

271
00:13:33,666 --> 00:13:36,166
I can't tell how many
of the goblins are still alive,

272
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:38,208
but I hear strange footsteps
coming this way.

273
00:13:38,291 --> 00:13:40,458
-[groans]
-[SHAMAN] Here they come!

274
00:13:40,541 --> 00:13:42,625
[arrows clinking]

275
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:44,083
[growling]

276
00:13:45,083 --> 00:13:46,666
[rumbling]

277
00:13:48,416 --> 00:13:50,083
[growls]

278
00:13:50,166 --> 00:13:52,208
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
A hob. No.

279
00:13:52,291 --> 00:13:54,541
[growling]

280
00:13:54,625 --> 00:13:55,916
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
A goblin champion.

281
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,208
[shatters]

282
00:13:57,291 --> 00:13:58,541
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
We'll cut through them.

283
00:13:58,625 --> 00:14:00,875
Allow my blade to assist
you however it can.

284
00:14:00,958 --> 00:14:03,000
[GOBLINS shouting]

285
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,041
Wait! Are you...?

286
00:14:18,875 --> 00:14:19,750
[grunts]

287
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,375
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] Six.
-[GOBLIN grunting]

288
00:14:27,458 --> 00:14:28,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Don't hold anything back.

289
00:14:28,916 --> 00:14:30,500
[PRIEST]
Understood.

290
00:14:40,208 --> 00:14:42,375
[ARCHER] Damn it!
There's too many of them.

291
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:45,000
No use complaining, long-ears,
keep fighting.

292
00:14:45,083 --> 00:14:49,291
-You holding up over there?
-I'm trying to, but it's hard.

293
00:14:50,625 --> 00:14:52,458
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Seventeen.

294
00:14:53,833 --> 00:14:55,125
[body thuds]

295
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:59,666
[GOBLIN grunting]

296
00:15:06,375 --> 00:15:08,416
[HOB roars]

297
00:15:11,625 --> 00:15:13,250
It took down Goblin Slayer!

298
00:15:13,333 --> 00:15:16,166
Say something, Orcbolg.
Are you hurt?

299
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:19,958
[GOBLIN SLAYER spits, gurgles]
No. No!

300
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:23,083
[whimpering]

301
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,416
[crying]

302
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:29,291
[PRIESTESS]
No.

303
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,791
-[screaming] No!
-[growling]

304
00:15:31,875 --> 00:15:34,208
-[shatters]
-Priestess! The miracle!

305
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,916
How did they
breach the barrier?

306
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:39,083
[ARCHER] Calm down
and concentrate, damn it!

307
00:15:39,166 --> 00:15:41,958
Don't give up. Fight them off.

308
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:43,541
[grunting]

309
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:50,291
Diabolical beasts!
Unhand her!

310
00:15:50,375 --> 00:15:51,958
-[ARCHER screams]
-[fabric ripping]

311
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:54,958
-[whimpering]
-[thudding footsteps]

312
00:15:56,208 --> 00:15:57,083
[yelps]

313
00:15:58,166 --> 00:16:00,583
[HOB growls]

314
00:16:00,666 --> 00:16:02,916
Please, don't hurt me.

315
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,791
[growling]

316
00:16:05,875 --> 00:16:07,625
[PRIESTESS whimpering]

317
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:10,083
-[growls]
-[PRIESTESS shrieks]

318
00:16:10,166 --> 00:16:12,000
[whimpering]

319
00:16:12,083 --> 00:16:13,916
-[HOB growling]
-[PRIESTESS shrieks]

320
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:17,500
-[roars]
-[screaming]

321
00:16:18,875 --> 00:16:21,333
[screaming continuing]

322
00:16:21,416 --> 00:16:23,958
[screaming echoing]

323
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,291
[screaming continuing]

324
00:16:32,791 --> 00:16:34,291
[screaming]

325
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:35,625
Bastards!

326
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,375
[growling]

327
00:16:42,458 --> 00:16:44,125
[cackling]

328
00:16:44,208 --> 00:16:48,083
[MALE VOICE] You think you have
the strength to slay goblins?

329
00:16:48,166 --> 00:16:49,625
[PRIESTESS screaming]

330
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:52,333
[MALE VOICE]
You just sat there and watched,

331
00:16:52,416 --> 00:16:55,000
while they raped and pillaged.

332
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:57,708
[echoing]
You are powerless.

333
00:16:57,791 --> 00:16:59,833
[dice clack]

334
00:17:04,583 --> 00:17:06,291
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Shit.

335
00:17:14,125 --> 00:17:15,791
[debris clatters]

336
00:17:18,500 --> 00:17:20,541
[bottle clinking]

337
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:23,750
Huh?

338
00:17:23,833 --> 00:17:25,625
[grumbles]

339
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,750
[blood squelches]

340
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:31,291
[cloth rips]

341
00:17:32,875 --> 00:17:34,916
[GOBLINS chattering]

342
00:17:36,791 --> 00:17:38,625
Help me.

343
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,375
[gasping]

344
00:17:43,541 --> 00:17:45,000
[gasps]

345
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:47,625
[HOB growls]

346
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:48,791
[HOB]
Huh?

347
00:17:48,875 --> 00:17:51,000
[gagging]

348
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:55,958
♪

349
00:17:57,625 --> 00:18:00,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER grunting]

350
00:18:09,791 --> 00:18:11,375
[GOBLIN SLAYER] I've heard
the weapon of choice

351
00:18:11,458 --> 00:18:14,458
for some assassins
is rope made of human hair.

352
00:18:14,541 --> 00:18:18,375
Now I see why.
It doesn't break easily.

353
00:18:18,458 --> 00:18:20,958
The ultimate way
to crush someone's neck.

354
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:24,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER grunts]

355
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:25,916
[HOB roaring]

356
00:18:27,083 --> 00:18:28,791
[HOB roars]

357
00:18:29,875 --> 00:18:31,208
[shouts]

358
00:18:33,583 --> 00:18:35,916
Get her healed!
We'll cover your back.

359
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,333
Thank you for your aid.

360
00:18:39,333 --> 00:18:41,708
You've saved me.

361
00:18:41,791 --> 00:18:44,541
Thanks, and I guess
I owe you a favor, Dwarf.

362
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:46,875
Consider that my expression
of elven gratitude

363
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:48,291
and don't let it go
to your head.

364
00:18:48,375 --> 00:18:50,000
You were just on
the verge of tears.

365
00:18:50,083 --> 00:18:52,583
Glad to see you've
got your spunk back.

366
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:54,500
[ARCHER]
You know it! Orcbolg!

367
00:18:54,583 --> 00:18:56,625
-[SHAMAN] Beard-cutter!
-[PRIEST] Sir Goblin Slayer!

368
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:02,125
[ARCHER]
Kill it!

369
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:03,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER screaming]

370
00:19:03,750 --> 00:19:06,000
[MALE VOICE]
Onward unto death!

371
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:10,458
Die like a nail
hammered into a coffin!

372
00:19:12,375 --> 00:19:14,041
[HOB choking]

373
00:19:14,125 --> 00:19:16,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Now, goblins, take a good look!

374
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:21,875
[roars]

375
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:24,000
-[grunts]
-[body thuds]

376
00:19:24,958 --> 00:19:27,458
[GOBLINS murmuring]

377
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:31,625
[GOBLIN SLAYER groans]
Which one of you is next?

378
00:19:33,208 --> 00:19:34,416
Is it you?

379
00:19:34,500 --> 00:19:37,833
[GOBLINS whimpering]

380
00:19:37,916 --> 00:19:39,291
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Or you?

381
00:19:39,375 --> 00:19:41,333
[GOBLINS whimpering]

382
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:43,333
[HOB groans]

383
00:19:46,291 --> 00:19:48,083
[GOBLINS whimpering]

384
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:49,583
[GOBLIN SLAYER groans]

385
00:19:49,666 --> 00:19:51,708
[GOBLINS shrieking]

386
00:19:54,625 --> 00:19:56,666
[GOBLIN SLAYER groaning]

387
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
[retches]

388
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:10,541
[ARCHER grunts]

389
00:20:10,625 --> 00:20:12,541
Steady yourself.

390
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER groans]
You okay?

391
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:17,083
Well, mostly.
But you're not, right?

392
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:20,375
That goblin champion
injured you pretty badly.

393
00:20:20,458 --> 00:20:24,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER] Yeah.
And the girl? Is she alive?

394
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:26,708
Barely.
Can you walk?

395
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:28,750
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
I can try.

396
00:20:28,833 --> 00:20:31,125
[ARCHER crying]

397
00:20:31,208 --> 00:20:33,583
There. Up you go.

398
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:35,000
Now, I'm willing to bet

399
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:38,333
you've still got some strength
under that armor.

400
00:20:38,416 --> 00:20:39,833
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
Yeah.

401
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:41,875
[SHAMAN chuckling]

402
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:43,625
Bless the stars.

403
00:20:43,708 --> 00:20:45,541
I'm not certain
how we are alive,

404
00:20:45,625 --> 00:20:47,791
but I'm ever so thankful we are.

405
00:20:47,875 --> 00:20:49,375
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
How is she?

406
00:20:49,458 --> 00:20:52,166
[PRIEST] She's grievously
wounded, but she will survive.

407
00:20:52,250 --> 00:20:53,791
Had the wound been any deeper,

408
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:56,041
there would've been nothing
I could do to help.

409
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,875
-[GOBLIN SLAYER] I see.
-[gasps]

410
00:21:00,291 --> 00:21:04,833
[weakly]
I'm so... sorry.

411
00:21:08,583 --> 00:21:10,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
You shouldn't worry.

412
00:21:10,208 --> 00:21:13,250
Goblin... Slayer,

413
00:21:13,333 --> 00:21:17,125
I couldn't protect... us.

414
00:21:17,208 --> 00:21:19,208
[GOBLIN SLAYER]
These things happen.

415
00:21:19,291 --> 00:21:20,250
[coughs]

416
00:21:20,333 --> 00:21:23,000
[gasps]

417
00:21:23,083 --> 00:21:25,125
[GOBLIN SLAYER groans]

418
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,916
[dice clack]

419
00:21:34,000 --> 00:21:35,583
[gasping]

420
00:21:35,666 --> 00:21:38,000
[gasps]

421
00:21:40,541 --> 00:21:42,583
[blood drips echoing]

422
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:49,041
♪

423
00:23:18,166 --> 00:23:20,208
♪

424
00:23:34,666 --> 00:23:36,666
[canary singing]

425
00:25:12,541 --> 00:25:14,583
[dice clack]

